programmes.show_description: Dr Dev Shah struggles to treat a football fan who has a painful ball of fat below his ribcage. Dr Emma McMullen deals with a large liquid-filled neck cyst.

programmes.show_name: Call the Bailiffs: Time to Pay Up!
programmes.show_description: ...Pay Up! In London, Scott and police officers remove squatters from a council-owned building where they've been living for nearly a year. But one woman barricades herself in a room.
A couple from Kent face losing their house because of a nightmare tenant, and a residential home is found to have been turned into a brothel.
Dr Amir Khan removes the biggest lipoma he has ever seen from Nigel's chest. Vanda was told she had only two years to live, but Dr Chris Harris offers a more positive prognosis.
David and Brennan try to build a case that Gough's the killer. Lisa uses her journalistic resources to try to connect Gough to the kidnappings. Gill threatens to blackmail David. (Ep5)
Challengers 'Brahms & Liszt Challenge' take on the mighty Eggheads, aiming to win the rolling prize fund.

We meet a couple of new characters who are grafting hard in Spain to find their spot in the sun.
We meet East London baker Lee, who has transferred his skills to Benidorm, where he's offering a British alternative to traditional Spanish baked goods.
TM Eye's teams are making an impact in Ealing - if stolen goods are valued at over Â£2000, the team will push for a prosecution. And in Newton Abbott a toy store is targeted. (Ep5)
PC Andy Swift is patrolling on the M1 when a car he flags down speeds off. A chase at speeds up to 120mph ensues. Sgt Steve Hughes uses his experience to help with a drunk man.
The team chase a suspect lorry that refuses to stop, and six police cars track an 18-tonne lorry when its driver heads the wrong way down a slip road into oncoming traffic.
Cameras follow traffic officers from various UK police forces, as they patrol major roads and deal with confrontations during their shifts.
Zippy the sniffer dog makes an interesting discovery and the team's new recruits are put to the test by a pair of suspected burglars.
The team pulls over a very angry driver and the Air Support Unit has its work cut out pursuing an athletic burglar.
The team joins forces with the chopper to track down a wanted criminal on a motorbike, and a young driver crashes straight into an unmarked police car.
A sportswoman's claim for loss of earnings falters at the start line and pet insurers expose a dog owner's canine con.
Kerrie expresses remorse over her past mistakes. Tane's trust in Harper wavers.
Tane and Harper go head-to-head. Kerrie's lies cause friction. Mali extends an olive branch.
Documentary series filmed inside the Ridge Medical Practice in Bradford. Elderly patient Elizabeth is suffering with persistent bleeding, a potential sign of cancer.
With Barnsley Casualty declared a crime scene, the team have to deal with emergencies inside and outside the hospital. Doctor Dave needs to negotiate with the police.
Cara has fallen 50 metres down a waterfall. She has multiple obvious injuries that need urgent care, but Dr Richard Fawcett must also investigate hidden internal injuries.
A knife fight leads to a suspect headbutting a windscreen, there's a suspected terrorist bomb at a shopping centre, and a car colliding with a telegraph pole brings down a live wire.
Dr Toby Nelson checks a patient's back and finds a pre-cancerous mole, Dr Emma McMullen inspects a lipoma on a patient's buttock, and Dr Dev Shah treats a collection of skin tags.
A retired couple pay the price when their tenants stop paying rent and invite their abusive friends in to squat.
A landlord calls in help when some clued-up squatters take over a disused pub, and a widow faces trouble when she tries to evict a family who owe her thousands in rent.
Harrow Council visit vulnerable tenants paying through the nose to live in uninhabitable conditions, including one man living in a plywood shed on the roof of a building.
Lisa finds out the investigation has been halted. Lisa and Brennan follow a lead on the killer and make their way to an abandoned slaughterhouse to investigate. (Ep6)

The fight against the rise of shoplifting. In London's West End undercover officers pursue a known "dipper", and in Birmingham a stolen bank card scam becomes threatening. (Ep1)
In Coventry, a prolific shoplifter is caught, and claims he steals out of necessity. At a QD store someone thinks they can get away with not paying for their Christmas shopping. (Ep2)
Documentary series. A young mum lets a young couple stay in her house for free, but ends up locked out of her own home. Nick discovers that his absent tenant has sublet his house.
Catching up with the victims and villains of the rental market. Rachel intended to rent out her cottage for three months; four years later, her tenant is still there.
Craig has been battling to get his property back after three months of no rent. Terry was relieved to get his home back, before Sophia called the police.
Documentary series. In Bristol, Jon's dream of turning a former tram staion into flats was derailed by squatters, has he managed to get things back on track?
CCTV exposes the lies of a man who claims that a collision left him with serious injuries. Police crack a lost watch scam.
